The paper deals with adversarial attacks on machine learning models, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR). The proposed method involves modifying the gradient of a function, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The experiments are conducted on image datasets, which suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another likely sub-category. The use of watermarking schemes also suggests multimedia (cs.MM) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of machine learning to detect and recover from attacks, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
